<h2>Does This Replace Fixing My Email?</h2>

<p>No — and it shouldn't. Configuring your email properly (SMTP plugin, SPF/DKIM records, a reputable sending service) is still worthwhile. Email is your archive and your formal communication record. Do both:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Fix your email delivery so it's as reliable as possible</li>
  <li>Add Telegram so you're covered when email fails anyway</li>
</ul>

<p>Redundancy isn't a sign that one system is broken. It's a sign that the outcome matters enough to protect twice.</p>
